    description: 'Nintendo\'s original villain — a massive gorilla who kidnaps Pauline and hurls barrels at the hapless Jumpman — Donkey Kong was eventually redeemed and reborn as a heroic protagonist in the Super Nintendo era. His journey from antagonist to icon is one of gaming\'s great character rehabilitations.',
    longDescription: 'Donkey Kong holds the unusual distinction of having debuted as a villain before being reinvented as a hero, a transformation that required more than a decade of franchise evolution. The original 1981 arcade game established him as an elemental threat — enormous, implacable, defined by his barrel-throwing fury — and his role as the obstacle that Jumpman (later Mario) must overcome. The character was dormant for years as Mario\'s franchise eclipsed his, but Rare\'s Donkey Kong Country in 1994 performed a remarkable rehabilitation: DK was reimagined as a cool, laid-back hero protecting his island home, with Cranky Kong retconned as the original antagonist of the 1981 arcade game. This creative maneuver gave Nintendo a second major platformer franchise and transformed Donkey Kong from a villain into one of gaming\'s most beloved protagonists.',
