    description: 'The patriarch of the vampire-hunting Belmont clan, Simon wields the legendary Vampire Killer whip against Dracula and his supernatural legions. His games defined the action-platformer formula on the NES and established a gothic aesthetic that influenced horror gaming for decades.',
    longDescription: 'Simon Belmont is the archetypal monster hunter — stoic, determined, armed with ancestral weapon and holy sub-weapons, walking into darkness because someone must. Konami\'s Castlevania franchise built an entire mythology around the Belmont bloodline\'s centuries-long war against Dracula, and Simon is its founding figure in gaming terms, the ancestor whose actions set events in motion for generations of successors. The original Castlevania and its sequel Simon\'s Quest on the NES established the franchise\'s distinctive blend of punishing action gameplay, gothic horror aesthetics, and atmospheric music — elements that would eventually give rise to the Metroidvania genre when Symphony of the Night grafted RPG elements onto the series\' DNA. Simon\'s visual design, a broad-shouldered warrior in leather and chain-mail, communicated muscular competence without the technological augmentation of a Samus or the supernatural abilities of later Belmonts, making him feel grounded in a way his successors often were not.',
